description.narrative: The objective of the Public Financial Management Reform Project for Vietnam is to strengthen the recipient's capacity to plan, execute, and report on its budget and to improve the transparency and accountability of the budgetary systems and processes. The closing date of the project will be extended from February 28, 2013 to October 31, 2013. The extension is necessary to ensure successful hand-over of the treasury and budget management information system (TABMIS) from the contractor to the Ministry of Finance (MoF) and complete the remaining critical activities. Reallocation will bring the following changes: (1) delivering TABMIS under a turn-key contract covering both goods and operating costs; and (2) utilizing the remaining fund to meet the additional consultancy and training needs in order to fully achieve the objectives of the project.
